<FIRST>r a AM-ChildKiller     04-13 0271</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Child Killer,0277</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nurse Who Killed Her Children Is Released From Mental Hospital</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SAMUEL MAULL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pediatric nurse who killed two of her babies
and tried to kill a third was released Wednesday from the mental
hospital where she has been held since she was acquitted of the
deaths by reason of insanity.
   Ann Green, confined to the Kirby Forensic Psychiatric Center for
the past 37 days, would not be dangerous if released, state mental
health officials, Dr. Art Dubow and Dr. David Webber, said.
   ``I'm happy to be free,'' Mrs. Green, 43, said as she left the
courtroom where she was tried for killing her children. ``I hope
other women and other people understand what I went through and
that it helps them.''
   Mrs. Green was freed pending another hearing April 27, but her
freedom has restrictions. She is required to continue treatment,
and must have no working, residential or caretaking situation
involving children, including her one surviving child.
   Mrs. Green's attorney, Michael Dowd, objected to the conditions
that bar her contact with children. Dowd said Mrs. Green had been
dangerous only to her own infants under stress and this was due to
post-partum depression.
   Mrs. Green was acquitted last September of two counts of murder
for smothering her newborn children in 1980 and 1982 and one count
of attempted murder for trying to kill a third in 1985.
   The third child, Larry Jr., was saved by a neighbor after Mrs.
Green falsely yelled to her that the boy had inexplicably stopped
breathing. Larry Jr., 3, is now living with relatives.
</TEXT>
