<FIRST>r i PM-Chile-Cocaine     04-13 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Chile-Cocaine,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Raid Yacht, Seize 570 Pounds Of Cocaine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALCAHUANO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police raided a U.S.-registered yacht
in this southern port and found 570 pounds of Miami-bound cocaine _
Chile's largest seizure of the narcotic, a police general said
today.
   Two Colombians and an Ecuadoran were arrested in the raid late
Wednesday in the port 350 miles south of Santiago after residents
tipped off officials that those aboard were spending large amounts
of money in town, police said.
   Police Gen. Rene Varas said the drug cache found aboard the
Florida-registered Marco Polo has a street value of $160 million.
He said it was Chile's largest cocaine seizure.
   Among those arrested was the yacht's owner and skipper, a
Colombian who police identified as Miguel Eduardo Taylor, 41.
   The boat arrived from Colombia and was scheduled to leave
Thursday or Friday for Miami, said Varas.
   Among the world's largest cocaine busts was the seizure of
22,000 pounds of the drug in Colombia in March 1984.
</TEXT>
