<HEAD>Bechtel Chief Alden Yates Dies Of Cancer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alden P. Yates, president of Bechtel Group
Inc., has died of cancer. He was 60.
   Yates, who joined the engineering and construction company in
1953, died Wednesday.
   He became president of the company in 1983, succeeding George
Shultz, who left to become U.S. secretary of state. The two were
the only presidents who were not members of the Bechtel family.
   Yates was a member of the National Academy of Engineering, the
California Business Roundtable, and the San Francisco Opera
Association.
   Survivors include his wife, Dawn, and their six children and six
grandchildren.
