<HEAD>Barclays Bank Employees Defy Back-to-Work Order</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GABORONE, Botswana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nearly 2,000 Barclays Bank employees
Thursday defied a government order to end a week-old strike that
has closed all 18 branches of the country's largest commercial bank.
   The employees are protesting a proposed new salary structure
that would give 20 percent increases to senior employees but only
10 percent increases to clerks and other junior staff. The
employees' union is demanding a 20 percent raise for all.
   On Wednesday, Labor Minister Englishman Kgabo declared the
strike illegal and ordered employees to return to work. He did not
specify what action would be taken against the strikers if they did
not obey, but participants in an illegal walkout can be punished by
fines or jail terms.
