<FIRST>r i AM-Stewart-Melee     04-13 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Stewart-Melee,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Disperse Fans Trying to Mob Rod Stewart, 150 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GUADALAJARA, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guards used night sticks and tear gas
to disperse hundreds of fans who tried to mob rock singer Rod
Stewart at a concert, and more than 150 people were injured, police
said Thursday.
   None of those injured Wednesday was hurt seriously enough to be
hospitalized, police said. All were treated by Red Cross volunteers
for bruises and tear gas inhalation.
   About 1,200 special guards and city police were deployed to
handle the crowd of 60,000 fans.
   More than 1,600 fans tried to mob Stewart as he entered the
concert hall, prompting the action by the guards.
   Halfway into the concert, blown fuses plunged the hall into
darkness for more than 20 minutes.
   Stewart, on a tour of several Latin American countries, was
given several ovations at the end of the appearance.
   Disturbances also marred his concerts last week in Queretaro,
northwest of Mexico City and in the northern industrial city of
Monterrey.
</TEXT>
