<SECOND>AM-Escapee Haircut,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>Escaped Prisoner Caught After Stop At Barber Shop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILLINGS, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A prisoner who escaped from a courthouse
stopped two blocks away to get a shave and a haircut and was
captured afterward still wearing his handcuffs and a waist chain.
   Cathy Brekke said the man came into her barbershop Tuesday and
was in a hurry to have his hair cut and his beard and moustache
shaved off.
   ``He was sweating like a pig and wouldn't take off his jacket,''
she said. ``He was real uncomfortable when he was getting his hair
shampooed. He told me he'd been hit by a truck.''
   Brekke said she didn't noticie anything unusual until he
remained in the shop to use the telephone after his haircut.
   She said she ``kept seeing something metal,'' though the
handcuffs were under his sleeves and the chain around his waist was
inside his sportscoat. She finally realized he was handcuffed and
called police from a nearby restaurant.
   Police arrested Rick Savaria, 33, who had escaped two hours
earlier from a line of eight prisoners at the county courthouse,
said Undersheriff Chuck Maxwell.
   Maxwell said authorities will seek felony escape charges against
Savaria, who had been awaiting sentencing on a theft charge.
</TEXT>
