<HEAD>East German Flees To West Out Of Loneliness For Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German man slipped past
communist guards and over border fences into West Germany out of
loneliness for his wife who had defected earlier, officials said
Thursday.
   The escape occurred Wednesday night near the West German town of
Helmstedt, 95 miles east of Hanover, said West German border police.
   The East German told officials his wife had been living in West
Germany since deciding not to return to her communist homeland from
a visit, police said. Neither the man nor woman was identified.
   According to a statement, the escapee said he wanted to be
reunited with his wife and that he was ``having difficulties with
his employer and officials'' because of her defection.
   Police did not say how long his wife had been living in West
Germany.
