<HEAD>JCS Chairman Reviewing National Defense University</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff has
formed a committee to review the curriculum and role of the
National Defense University in military eduction, the Pentagon said
Thursday.
   The committee will be chaired by retired Adm. Robert L.J. Long
and has been asked to complete its study by September.
   Adm. William J. Crowe, the chairman of the Joint Chiefs, has
asked 10 other military professionals and prominent civilians to
join Long on the panel, the Pentagon added.
   The National Defense University, located at Fort McNair in
Washington, D.C., includes the National War College, the Industrial
College of the Armed Forces and the Armed Forces Staff College. It
is considered the senior-level military university for officers
working in ``joint'' specialties that cut across service lines.
