night in Los Angeles.
   On April 26, the president will visit former President Reagan in
Los Angeles, and later address the Texas State Legislature in
Austin.
   On April 27, he will participate in an anti-drug event in Miami
with the Coast Guard, the Customs Service and the Drug Enforcement
Conference.
   He will travel to New York City on April 30, to attend church
and participate in an event marking the Bicentennial of the
American Presidency.
   He will also deliver five commencement addresses this spring,
White House press secretary Marlin Fitzwater announced in a
statement on Bush's travel plans.
   They include Texas A&amp;M in College Station on May 12; Alcorn
State University in Lorman, Miss., on May 13; Mississippi State
University in Starkville on May 13; Boston University on May 21 and
the United States Coast Guard Academy in New London, Conn., on May
24.
