<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     04-13 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stocks Fall in Early Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell in London Thursday, and dealers
said the market suffered from a lack of buying interest.
   Most market participants apparently chose to overlook late
morning British economic indicators.
   The market was described as featureless, and participants said
they were waiting for Friday's flood of American economic
indicators and more British indicators, as well as the close of the
current two-week trading account on the London Stock Exchange.
   At midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index
was down 8.3 points, at 2,204.7.
   Volume at midday was 250.0 million shares, compared with 227.3
million shares at the same time Wednesday.
