<HEAD>Formica Corp. Says It Has Approved Merger Agreement With FM Acquisition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYNE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Formica Corp. announced Thursday it has
approved a revised merger agreement with a management-led investor
group which will pay about $365 million in cash for the laminated
products company.
   The agreement does not allow Formica to accept offers from other
companies.
   The $19-per-share bid by FM Acquisition Corp. includes the
assumption of Formica debt.
   Formica announced Monday that it rejected a $243 million
takeover from FM Acquisition, one of several offers made for the
company in recent months. That offer was $18.75 per share.
   Formica also announced Thursday that an unidentified industrial
corporation, which had reportedly offered $20 per share for the
company, has withdrawn its offer.
   Formica makes laminated products used in kitchen countertops and
tables.
   FM Acquisition was organized by Formica managers and Dillon Read
&amp; Co. Inc.
