<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Intel     04-13 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Intel,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Intel Earnings Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Intel Corp.'s earnings rose slightly
in the first quarter in spite of a January prediction by the
computer chip maker that they would decline, the company said
Thursday.
   The increase, to $97 million from $94 million a year earlier,
was the result of cost controls, a good factory performance and
strong March results, Intel said.
   Earnings per share declined to 52 cents from 54 cents a year ago
due to an increase in the number of shares outstanding, the company
said.
   Revenues totaled $713 million, up from $636 million a year ago.
   Andrew Grove, the company president, said the ``outlook
brightened as the quarter progressed.''
