<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
247,628 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
250,056, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 245,290 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 160,652 cars this week,
compared with 159,295 a week ago and 158,565 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,976,
compared with last week's 90,761 and last year's 86,725.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,436 cars this week, up from
21,980 a week ago and last year's 24,265.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,077,
compared with 21,985 a week ago and 20,434 in the same week last
year.
