<FIRST>u f AM-BritishStocks     04-13 0209</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-British Stocks,0216</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   London Stock Echange prices shrugged off
potentially worrisome data showing an acceleration in the
underlying rate of increase of British average earnings to close
only slightly lower Thursday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed down
4.3 points, or 0.2 percent, at 2,028.7. At its best, the index was
down 1.6 points at late afternoon, after having dropped 14.9 points
at mid-morning.
   Light volume of 463.0 million shares was little changed from
Wednesday's 467.9 million shares.
   While the implications of the data could still return to haunt
the market, dealers said there was a lack of selling pressure as
participants awaited much more important economic statistics due
Friday.
   Those include the British retail price index for March, followed
later in the day by the U.S. producer price index for March and the
U.S. trade report for February.
   Thursday figures showed that average earnings in Britain grew at
an underlying annual rate of 9\ percent in February, compared with
9 percent in January.
   The figures were ``unequivocal bad news,'' said Robin Aspinall,
a market analyst at Schroder Securities. But he said Friday ``is a
much more important day. There is hardly anybody out there who is
daring to sell.''
</TEXT>
