<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-GeneralElectric     04-13 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-General Electric,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Earnings Up 18 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Electric Co. on Thursday
reported first quarter earnings jumped 18 percent over the same
1988 period in part because of especially strong sales increases in
plastics appliances.
   GE reported net income of $849 million, or 94 cents a share, on
revenue of $11.9 billion. That compares to earnings of $725
million, or 80 cents a share, on $10.5 billion in revenue a year
earlier.
   The revenue rise includes a 17 percent increase in the company's
GE Financial Services division. Its revenue was $2.8 billion in the
quarter compared to $2.4 billion in the first quarter of 1988.
   ``Sales increases were particularly strong in plastic,
appliances, industrial and power systems, and broadcasting, with
plastics and appliances helped somewhat by the Borg-Warner and and
Roper acquisitions,'' GE Chairman John F. Welch Jr. said.
   GE last year acquired Borg-Warner Corp. for $2.3 billion and
Roper Corp. for about $507 million.
