<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Coca-Cola     04-13 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Coca-Cola,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Posts 23.4 Percent Profit Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Coca-Cola Co. said Thursday its first-quarter
profit climbed 23.4 percent on a 6.2 percent rise in revenue.
   The soft-drink giant said it earned $259.8 million, or 72 cents
a share, in the first three months of this year compared with
$210.5 million, or 57 cents a share, a year earlier.
   First-quarter revenue rose to $1.99 billion from $1.87 billion a
year earlier.
   Retail case sales of the company's brands in the United States
were up 5 percent in the first quarter, while concentrate and syrup
shipments increased by 7 percent. International case sales
increased 8 percent and concentrate and syrup shipments in other
countries rose 6 percent.
   Equity income for the quarter was $2 million in contrast to a
$50 million equity loss in the first quarter of 1988, due to
one-time expenses at 49 percent-owned Columbia Pictures
Entertainment Inc.
